      "metadata": {
        "id": "323f1062"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Dataset Selection and Preparation\n",
        "\n",
        "For object recognition with YOLO, selecting an appropriate dataset and ensuring it's in a compatible format is crucial. Public datasets like COCO, PASCAL VOC, and Open Images are commonly used, but custom datasets can also be prepared.\n",
        "\n",
        "**YOLO-specific annotation format:**\n",
        "YOLO models typically require annotations in a specific text file format. Each image should have a corresponding `.txt` file with the same name, containing one row per object. Each row should follow this structure:\n",
        "\n",
        "`<object-class> <x_center> <y_center> <width> <height>`\n",
        "\n",
        "- `<object-class>`: Integer ID of the object class (starting from 0).\n",
        "- `<x_center>`, `<y_center>`, `<width>`, `<height>`: Float values, normalized relative to the image's width and height. These values range from 0.0 to 1.0.\n",
        "\n",
        "For demonstration purposes, we will download a small, pre-annotated dataset, `coco128`, which is a subset of the COCO dataset and is already formatted for YOLO. This will allow for quick setup and testing of YOLO models."
      ]
