      "source": [
        "## Summary:\n",
        "\n",
        "### Q&A\n",
        "\n",
        "**Which YOLO version and dataset were used for this implementation?**\n",
        "The implementation utilized the **YOLOv5** framework (specifically the YOLOv5s architecture) and the **COCO128** dataset, which is a small subset of the COCO dataset containing 128 images pre-formatted for YOLO.\n",
        "\n",
        "**What were the final performance metrics of the model?**\n",
        "After training for 3 epochs, the model achieved a Mean Average Precision at IoU 0.5 (**mAP50**) of **0.72** and an **mAP50-95** of **0.484**. The overall precision was **0.753** and recall was **0.612**.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Where are the training and detection results stored?**\n",
        "*   **Training weights and logs:** `yolov5/runs/train/coco128_results/`\n",
        "*   **Validation metrics:** `yolov5/runs/val/coco128_eval/`\n",
        "*   **Annotated images (Inference):** `yolov5/runs/detect/coco128_det/`\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### Data Analysis Key Findings\n",
        "\n",
        "*   **Model Efficiency:** The YOLOv5s model demonstrated a reasonable balance between speed and accuracy for a small-scale test. Inference speed on a CPU averaged between **331ms and 551ms** per image.\n",
        "*   **Transfer Learning Effectiveness:** By initializing the training with pre-trained weights (`yolov5s.pt`), the model reached a high mAP50 of **0.72** in only **3 epochs**, showcasing the power of transfer learning for rapid deployment.\n",
        "*   **Detection Consistency:** During the inference phase, the model successfully detected objects in **126 out of 128 images** (98.4%) using a confidence threshold of 0.25.\n",
        "*   **Class Performance:** High precision was specifically noted for common object classes such as `person`, `bird`, `cat`, and `stop sign`.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### Insights or Next Steps\n",
        "\n",
        "*   **Scale Training:** To improve the mAP50-95 (currently at 0.484) and generalizability, the model should be trained on the full COCO dataset for a higher number of epochs (e.g., 50-300).\n",
        "*   **Hardware Acceleration:** Transitioning from CPU to GPU (CUDA) for inference would significantly reduce latency, likely bringing the 331ms processing time down to the sub-20ms range for real-time applications.\n",
        "*   **Hyperparameter Tuning:** Fine-tuning the confidence threshold and NMS (Non-Maximum Suppression) IOU threshold during the `detect.py` phase could help reduce false negatives in the two images where no detections were found.\n"
